```

### Key SDK functions

**`createPluginRuntimeStore<T>(errorMessage: string)`** from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store`:
Returns `{ setRuntime, clearRuntime, tryGetRuntime, getRuntime }`.
Also exports `type PluginRuntime`.

**`createChatChannelPlugin(params)`** from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`:
Takes `{ base, security?, pairing?, threading?, outbound? }`.
The `base` object shape: `{ id, meta, capabilities, reload?, configSchema?, config, setup?, messaging?, status?, gateway?, ... }`.

**`defineChannelPluginEntry(options)`** from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`:
Takes `{ id, name, description, plugin, setRuntime?, configSchema?, registerCliMetadata?, registerFull? }`.

**`defineSetupPluginEntry(plugin)`** from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`:
Takes a plugin and returns `{ plugin }`.

**`attachChannelToResult(channel, result)`** from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result`:
Wraps an outbound result with channel info.

### ChannelPlugin type
```typescript
type ChannelPlugin<ResolvedAccount, Probe?, Audit?> = {
  id: ChannelId;
  meta: ChannelMeta;
  capabilities: ChannelCapabilities;
  reload?: { configPrefixes: string[] };
  config: ChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;  // required
  setup?: ChannelSetupAdapter;
  gateway?: ChannelGatewayAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  messaging?: ChannelMessagingAdapter;
  outbound?: ChannelOutboundAdapter;
  // ... many other optional adapters
};
```

## User requirements

Create 7 files in `extensions/pulseboard/`:

1. `package.json` — `@openclaw/pulseboard`, type module, openclaw block with channel metadata
2. `openclaw.plugin.json` — id `pulseboard`, channels array, minimal configSchema
3. `src/types.ts` — `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` interfaces
4. `src/runtime.ts` — runtime store using `createPluginRuntimeStore`
5. `src/channel.ts` — full channel plugin using `createChatChannelPlugin`
6. `index.ts` — entry using `defineChannelPluginEntry`
7. `setup-entry.ts` — setup entry using `defineSetupPluginEntry`

Key: the user says to use `getChatChannelMeta` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`, but as noted above, this function only accepts core channel IDs. The plan should define meta inline instead. 

The user wants stubs for most adapters — no actual PulseBoard API integration needed.

Design a detailed implementation plan with exact file contents for each of the 7 files, noting the getChatChannelMeta deviation.

